 ## Model and Mode
 
-### `/model <name>`
+### `/model <name>[:effort]`
 
-Switch to a different model. Accepts model IDs or display names (case-insensitive). For reasoning models you can also pass an effort level as a second argument:
+Switch to a different model. Accepts model IDs or display names
+(case-insensitive). For reasoning models, pass the effort as either a pi-style
+colon suffix or a second argument:
 
 ```
 /model grok-build
 /model Grok Build
 /model Reasoning X high
+/model openai-codex/gpt-5.5:xhigh
 ```
 
+Provider-prefixed IDs such as `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` explicitly select the
+provider. The suffix is parsed from the last colon only after trying the whole
+string as an exact model ID, so IDs that contain colons continue to work.
+Supported canonical levels are `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, and
+`xhigh` (subject to the selected model's offered levels).
+
 Aliases: `/m`
 
